1
00:00:32,166 --> 00:00:34,208
[KAREN]
You're nothing to me, Amano!

2
00:00:34,291 --> 00:00:36,416
And you, you suck at games!

3
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:39,541
It's not like I enjoyed spending
time with you or anything!

4
00:00:39,625 --> 00:00:41,041
So, there!

5
00:00:41,125 --> 00:00:42,208
[KEITA] Keep up the good work
with the game club, Tendo.

6
00:00:42,291 --> 00:00:44,666
I'm rooting for you!
I mean that!

7
00:00:44,750 --> 00:00:47,125
[KAREN cries]
Sure.

8
00:00:47,208 --> 00:00:48,416
Okay.

9
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:50,458
[KAREN cries]

10
00:00:50,541 --> 00:00:51,833
[KAREN yelps]

11
00:00:51,916 --> 00:00:54,291
[KAREN cries]

12
00:00:54,375 --> 00:00:57,625
[KAREN screams]

13
00:00:57,708 --> 00:00:59,416
[TASUKU]
What the hell...?

14
00:02:34,166 --> 00:02:35,916
[MIKA]
Huh? What was that?

15
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:37,250
Tendo ran outta here crying!

16
00:02:37,333 --> 00:02:39,541
[MASAYA] Was that, like,
relationship drama?

17
00:02:39,625 --> 00:02:40,916
[FEMALE STUDENT 2A]
Nah. I think I heard Tendo

18
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,416
say something about a club.

19
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:43,666
If you really wanna know,

20
00:02:43,750 --> 00:02:45,916
we could ask Amano what
they were talkin' about.

21
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,125
Don't look at me!

22
00:02:47,208 --> 00:02:49,166
[TASUKU]
Asking him ain't gonna work.

23
00:02:49,250 --> 00:02:52,000
Not unless one of you guys
speaks nerd fluently.

24
00:02:52,083 --> 00:02:53,291
[MASAYA]
Damn, Tasuku!

25
00:02:53,375 --> 00:02:54,958
[STUDENTS laugh]

26
00:02:55,041 --> 00:02:58,000
[TASUKU]
Seriously, what's your deal?

27
00:02:59,083 --> 00:03:00,333
[MIKA]
I dunno what it is,

28
00:03:00,416 --> 00:03:02,375
but something about
him ticks me off.

29
00:03:02,458 --> 00:03:03,708
--[TASUKU] Why?
--No reason!

30
00:03:03,791 --> 00:03:06,125
Just seems like he's
kinda stuck-up, y'know?

31
00:03:06,208 --> 00:03:08,458
Like he's too good to
talk to anyone else.

32
00:03:08,541 --> 00:03:10,750
[DAIKI] He does kinda have
that "high and mighty" vibe,

33
00:03:10,833 --> 00:03:12,416
now that you mention it.

34
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:14,958
Where the hell does he get
off lookin' down on us

35
00:03:15,041 --> 00:03:16,583
when he's nothin' but a loser.

36
00:03:16,666 --> 00:03:18,333
Yeah.

37
00:03:18,416 --> 00:03:19,458
[TASUKU]
Pretty lame.

38
00:03:19,541 --> 00:03:20,791
[ALL gasp]

39
00:03:20,875 --> 00:03:22,291
Uhhh.

40
00:03:22,375 --> 00:03:25,791
I was just thinkin' about how
lame his life's gotta be.

41
00:03:25,875 --> 00:03:27,500
[DAIKI]
Oh, that's what you meant.

42
00:03:27,583 --> 00:03:28,791
[MASAYA]
For a second there,

43
00:03:28,875 --> 00:03:30,666
I thought you were throwin'
shade at us, man.

44
00:03:30,750 --> 00:03:31,958
Yeah right.

45
00:03:32,041 --> 00:03:33,541
C'mon, you guys are my buddies.

46
00:03:33,625 --> 00:03:35,541
[laughs]

47
00:03:37,125 --> 00:03:39,208
When using an auxiliary verb,

48
00:03:39,291 --> 00:03:41,958
it's important to understand
the role of conjunctions

49
00:03:42,041 --> 00:03:44,250
within the idea being expressed.

50
00:03:44,333 --> 00:03:47,666
In other words, whatever
precedes the auxiliary verb...

51
00:03:47,750 --> 00:03:49,791
[TASUKU]
Damn nerd!

52
00:03:50,958 --> 00:03:52,666
[AGURI]
Tasuku!

53
00:03:52,750 --> 00:03:54,791
Eat with me, okay?

54
00:03:54,875 --> 00:03:56,125
Fine.

55
00:03:56,208 --> 00:03:58,916
Oh! I can't wait to charge
up on Tasuku-power!

56
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:01,875
[MIKA] It's crazy how much you
like Uehara, you know that?

57
00:04:01,958 --> 00:04:03,791
[laughs]

58
00:04:03,875 --> 00:04:06,791
I made the two of us a
super-adorable lunch!

59
00:04:06,875 --> 00:04:07,791
Ta-da!

60
00:04:07,875 --> 00:04:09,375
Look, it's a cute kitty!

61
00:04:09,458 --> 00:04:11,375
[BOYS]
Uh, sure.

62
00:04:11,458 --> 00:04:12,291
Uh...?

63
00:04:12,375 --> 00:04:13,416
[screams]

64
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:16,666
My food-kitty got all squished!

65
00:04:17,958 --> 00:04:19,083
[AGURI]
Hey, Tasuku!

66
00:04:19,166 --> 00:04:20,875
Y'know that one guy, Amano?

67
00:04:20,958 --> 00:04:22,041
He's in your class, isn't he?

68
00:04:22,125 --> 00:04:23,291
[TASUKU]
Yeah.

69
00:04:23,375 --> 00:04:25,500
Everyone in Class C was
talking about him today.

70
00:04:25,583 --> 00:04:28,541
Something about him totally
rejecting Karen Tendo.

71
00:04:28,625 --> 00:04:29,583
I don't care.

72
00:04:29,666 --> 00:04:31,125
That was so cold!

73
00:04:31,208 --> 00:04:33,500
You can't just talk to
your girlfriend like that.

74
00:04:33,583 --> 00:04:35,166
You think I'm too harsh?

75
00:04:35,250 --> 00:04:37,541
That's just the way I am.

76
00:04:37,625 --> 00:04:38,791
[gasps]

77
00:04:44,208 --> 00:04:46,000
[crash]

78
00:04:46,083 --> 00:04:48,958
[TASUKU] The truth is,
she caught me by surprise,

79
00:04:49,041 --> 00:04:50,458
so I said "yes."

80
00:04:50,541 --> 00:04:53,000
He can be as grumpy as he wants
'cause I love him, right?

81
00:04:53,083 --> 00:04:53,833
Uh-huh.

82
00:04:53,916 --> 00:04:54,791
[MIKA]
Really?

83
00:04:54,875 --> 00:04:56,666
And you're happy with that?

84
00:04:56,750 --> 00:04:57,875
As long as we're together,

85
00:04:57,958 --> 00:05:00,625
I'm the happiest girl
in the whole world!

86
00:05:01,958 --> 00:05:03,333
[FEMALE STUDENT 2A]
You think we're gonna all fit

87
00:05:03,416 --> 00:05:04,666
in the booth?

88
00:05:04,750 --> 00:05:06,833
I ran outta cash, Masaya.
Ya mind paying for it?

89
00:05:06,916 --> 00:05:09,250
[MASAYA]
Huh? You're such a mooch!

90
00:05:09,333 --> 00:05:10,583
[AGURI]
Where ya goin'?

91
00:05:10,666 --> 00:05:12,666
[TASUKU] Do the math,
I ain't fittin' in there.

92
00:05:12,750 --> 00:05:13,750
[AGURI]
Come on!

93
00:05:13,833 --> 00:05:15,416
Just hang out until we're done!

94
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:16,666
[TASUKU]
Gotta pee, anyway.

95
00:05:16,750 --> 00:05:18,875
[AGURI whines]

96
00:05:25,291 --> 00:05:29,250
♪♪♪

97
00:05:40,166 --> 00:05:42,500
What're you looking at, huh?

98
00:05:44,583 --> 00:05:50,416
[MIDDLE SCHOOL STUDENTS laugh]

99
00:05:53,875 --> 00:05:55,458
[TASUKU]
Yes!

100
00:05:56,541 --> 00:05:57,666
[TASUKU]
Damn it!

101
00:05:57,750 --> 00:06:00,333
When am I gonna stop
havin' these flashbacks?

102
00:06:00,416 --> 00:06:01,208
Uh?

103
00:06:01,291 --> 00:06:03,250
[TASUKU]
Aw, what the hell?!

104
00:06:03,333 --> 00:06:07,500
[laughs] Hey, I'm Keita Amano.

105
00:06:07,583 --> 00:06:09,291
We're kind of in class together.

106
00:06:09,375 --> 00:06:11,041
You think I don't know that?

107
00:06:11,125 --> 00:06:13,125
So, whatcha want?

108
00:06:13,208 --> 00:06:16,958
Since you're here, that must
mean you like games a lot, huh?

109
00:06:17,041 --> 00:06:19,250
Uh, sure.

110
00:06:19,333 --> 00:06:21,541
Never really thought about it.

111
00:06:24,041 --> 00:06:25,875
[gasps] That's cool.

112
00:06:25,958 --> 00:06:28,083
[KEITA]
Lemme see!

113
00:06:28,166 --> 00:06:31,208
I've never played it before,
but everyone talks it up.

114
00:06:31,291 --> 00:06:33,041
" <i>Paradigm of Phantasia.</i> "

115
00:06:33,125 --> 00:06:34,750
[KEITA]
This one's a masterpiece!

116
00:06:34,833 --> 00:06:38,208
No kidding, Uehara, you don't
know what you're missing out on!

117
00:06:38,291 --> 00:06:39,750
It's... that good?

118
00:06:39,833 --> 00:06:41,125
[KEITA]
Yeah!

119
00:06:41,208 --> 00:06:42,708
They pitched it like it was
going to revolutionize

120
00:06:42,791 --> 00:06:44,208
the <i>Paradigm</i> franchise,

121
00:06:44,291 --> 00:06:45,583
but it ended up being more of
the same when it came out,

122
00:06:45,666 --> 00:06:47,083
so fans gave it a lot of crap.

123
00:06:47,166 --> 00:06:49,375
But, then they realized it
was really well-executed,

124
00:06:49,458 --> 00:06:50,291
so they came around!

125
00:06:50,375 --> 00:06:52,166
It's awesome!

126
00:06:52,250 --> 00:06:53,791
[TASUKU]
Y'know, you could've stopped

127
00:06:53,875 --> 00:06:55,916
after you told me "yeah."

128
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,916
[gasping] I'm sorry.

129
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,958
I'm just really passionate
about the franchise.

130
00:07:00,041 --> 00:07:02,125
You don't gotta apologize
to me about it.

131
00:07:02,208 --> 00:07:03,500
Chill.

132
00:07:03,583 --> 00:07:06,500
Right! Thank you!
I guess I'll be going!

133
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:17,208
Uh?

134
00:07:20,083 --> 00:07:21,958
[TASUKU]
What the heck is he doing?

135
00:07:22,041 --> 00:07:23,541
Weirdo.

136
00:07:28,541 --> 00:07:31,166
[TASUKU] Don't tell me this
dude who loves gaming so much

137
00:07:31,250 --> 00:07:33,458
never goes to arcades.

138
00:07:33,541 --> 00:07:35,333
[sighs]

139
00:07:35,416 --> 00:07:37,166
[TASUKU]
Just... wait up a sec.

140
00:07:37,250 --> 00:07:38,750
What?! What did I do?!

141
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:42,375
[sighs] It's time you an'
me got down to business.

142
00:07:42,458 --> 00:07:45,250
Uh, that's sweet, but I'm
not really into other guys.

143
00:07:45,333 --> 00:07:48,291
That's not even remotely
where I was goin' with it.

144
00:07:48,375 --> 00:07:49,583
Whaddya say?

145
00:07:49,666 --> 00:07:51,416
We gonna play something?

146
00:07:51,500 --> 00:07:53,250
Your call, Amano.

147
00:07:53,333 --> 00:07:56,416
Yes! Yes, a thousand times over!

148
00:07:58,041 --> 00:07:59,958
[TASUKU] Is this the one
you wanna play, then?

149
00:08:00,041 --> 00:08:02,166
[KEITA] Mm-hm! I've always
thought it looked interesting,

150
00:08:02,250 --> 00:08:04,208
but I've never gotten
a chance to try it.

151
00:08:04,291 --> 00:08:06,208
Ah.

152
00:08:06,291 --> 00:08:08,125
I actually came
here once before,

153
00:08:08,208 --> 00:08:11,333
but I felt bad wasting people's
time watching the demo videos.

154
00:08:11,416 --> 00:08:12,750
So, what?

155
00:08:12,833 --> 00:08:14,791
You just went home without ever
having played the thing?

156
00:08:14,875 --> 00:08:17,208
Yeah. I guess I did.

157
00:08:17,291 --> 00:08:19,916
[TASUKU] How does this kid
survive without a spine?

158
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:23,791
And how did he have the
balls to reject Tendo?

159
00:08:23,875 --> 00:08:25,208
Tell me something.

160
00:08:25,291 --> 00:08:28,333
What kind of weirdness is going
on with you and Tendo?

161
00:08:28,416 --> 00:08:30,333
Huh? Uh, nothing!

162
00:08:30,416 --> 00:08:32,708
Why would you think
something like that?

163
00:08:32,791 --> 00:08:35,791
[TASUKU] Fine.
You don't gotta tell me squat.

164
00:08:35,875 --> 00:08:37,083
It's cool.

165
00:08:37,166 --> 00:08:39,583
So, uh. It's like this...

166
00:08:39,666 --> 00:08:43,666
[MIKA laughs] What the hell
kinda face was I making?

167
00:08:43,750 --> 00:08:44,916
Comedy gold!

168
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:46,875
This is no fun without Tasuku.

169
00:08:46,958 --> 00:08:50,041
If he doesn't come back,
I'm going home.

170
00:08:51,916 --> 00:08:55,875
[AGURI]
Huh...? Who's the tiptoe girl?

171
00:08:55,958 --> 00:08:58,750
[TASUKU]
Hm... So there's a game club.

172
00:08:58,833 --> 00:09:01,041
I didn't know our school
had that kinda thing.

173
00:09:01,125 --> 00:09:02,500
[KEITA]
Mm-hm.

174
00:09:02,583 --> 00:09:04,041
Here's what I'm not getting.

175
00:09:04,125 --> 00:09:05,666
How were the games
they play in the club

176
00:09:05,750 --> 00:09:08,291
that different from what you
wanna play all by yourself?

177
00:09:08,375 --> 00:09:09,791
It's weird.

178
00:09:09,875 --> 00:09:14,458
I'm not sure if I can explain it
in a way that makes sense.

179
00:09:14,541 --> 00:09:16,083
But you did want
friends that you could

180
00:09:16,166 --> 00:09:18,166
talk about video
games with, right?

181
00:09:18,250 --> 00:09:19,458
[KEITA]
Yeah, I did!

182
00:09:19,541 --> 00:09:20,958
Uh, do.

183
00:09:21,041 --> 00:09:22,583
Anyway...

184
00:09:22,666 --> 00:09:24,166
[TASUKU]
I can't let it shake me.

185
00:09:24,250 --> 00:09:26,250
Look, Uehara!
It's our turn to play!

186
00:09:26,333 --> 00:09:27,958
[sighs]

187
00:09:29,083 --> 00:09:31,125
You wanna mess with
the tutorial first?

188
00:09:31,208 --> 00:09:33,500
Nah, I'm good!
Let's do this thing!

189
00:09:33,583 --> 00:09:34,583
Okay.

190
00:09:34,666 --> 00:09:36,583
Time to grind this
newbie into dust.

191
00:09:36,666 --> 00:09:39,291
[KEITA]
'Kay! Go easy on me!

192
00:09:39,375 --> 00:09:41,291
[TASUKU]
Is this guy for real?

193
00:09:41,375 --> 00:09:44,291
♪♪♪

194
00:09:44,375 --> 00:09:48,666
[TASUKU] Amano's going with
the main character, huh?

195
00:09:48,750 --> 00:09:51,458
Uehara, how much have you
played this game before?

196
00:09:51,541 --> 00:09:52,708
[TASUKU]
None.

197
00:09:52,791 --> 00:09:54,416
I picked the bear-thing
'cause it looks cool.

198
00:09:54,500 --> 00:09:56,875
That's a good idea!

199
00:09:57,875 --> 00:10:00,333
[GAME ANNOUNCER 2A]
Round 1.

200
00:10:00,416 --> 00:10:01,500
Fight!

201
00:10:06,541 --> 00:10:08,833
[TASUKU] Well, at least
he's calmer than Aguri.

202
00:10:08,916 --> 00:10:10,416
Not like that's a big surprise.

203
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:12,791
Button-mashing!

204
00:10:12,875 --> 00:10:13,916
[TASUKU]
In a way, though,

205
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,791
she ends up being a
tougher opponent.

206
00:10:15,875 --> 00:10:17,750
Guys like Amano are predictable.

207
00:10:17,833 --> 00:10:18,916
Check it out.

208
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:20,958
[YU NARUKAMI grunting]

209
00:10:23,208 --> 00:10:26,041
[CHARACTERS chattering]

210
00:10:37,583 --> 00:10:38,708
Whoa!

211
00:10:38,791 --> 00:10:40,666
You're super amazing!

212
00:10:40,750 --> 00:10:43,000
[TASUKU]
No, you just suck.

213
00:10:44,083 --> 00:10:45,333
Time for my comeback!

214
00:10:45,416 --> 00:10:47,916
[GAME ANNOUNCER 2A]
Round 2.

215
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:48,750
Fight!

216
00:10:48,833 --> 00:10:50,458
[KEITA yelps]
Already?

217
00:10:50,541 --> 00:10:52,125
Wait! I wasn't ready!
Time-out, okay?

218
00:10:52,208 --> 00:10:53,958
[TASUKU]
It's just some fighting game.

219
00:10:54,041 --> 00:10:56,083
How come he's so into it?

220
00:10:57,833 --> 00:10:58,833
[gasps]

221
00:11:02,416 --> 00:11:06,625
[KEITA]
Ahh! I barely hurt you at all!

222
00:11:06,708 --> 00:11:08,750
[TASUKU] How can anyone
be so bad at this?

223
00:11:08,833 --> 00:11:12,166
Even a grade-school kid coulda
landed more punches!

224
00:11:13,791 --> 00:11:15,875
Wow, that was such a blast!

225
00:11:15,958 --> 00:11:17,500
Yeah, I guess.

226
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:21,916
So, what do we play next?

227
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:23,250
Huh?

228
00:11:23,333 --> 00:11:26,791
You gotta avenge my handing
you your ass, right?

229
00:11:26,875 --> 00:11:29,333
[gasps] How could I not?

230
00:11:29,416 --> 00:11:32,666
Over there! Let's try
that one next! Come on!

231
00:11:32,750 --> 00:11:34,208
[TASUKU chuckles]

232
00:11:53,583 --> 00:11:55,416
So what game should
we play next?

233
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:57,375
Look at you, knockin'
out all the games you

234
00:11:57,458 --> 00:11:59,666
couldn't play by your
lonesome. Pretty clever!

235
00:11:59,750 --> 00:12:00,833
Uh! What?!

236
00:12:00,916 --> 00:12:02,583
I don't know what
you're talking about!

237
00:12:02,666 --> 00:12:03,875
All righty, then!

238
00:12:03,958 --> 00:12:07,458
Now that we're hydrated,
let's get back to it!

239
00:12:07,541 --> 00:12:08,791
Weirdo.

240
00:12:09,958 --> 00:12:12,041
[TASUKU]
This happened once before.

241
00:12:12,125 --> 00:12:13,625
With her.

242
00:12:13,708 --> 00:12:14,916
Who was she?

243
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:16,250
Hm?

244
00:12:18,750 --> 00:12:22,041
[TASUKU]
Tendo's creepin', but why?

245
00:12:22,125 --> 00:12:23,791
Uh!

246
00:12:24,875 --> 00:12:28,333
Hey, what's the plan?

247
00:12:28,416 --> 00:12:30,875
[KEITA]
Uh. I think I'm gonna call it.

248
00:12:30,958 --> 00:12:32,083
Uh.

249
00:12:32,166 --> 00:12:34,583
[TASUKU] Oops, I forgot
they were even here.

250
00:12:34,666 --> 00:12:36,583
Thanks for all the fun today!

251
00:12:36,666 --> 00:12:37,750
See you later!

252
00:12:37,833 --> 00:12:39,375
Uh... Hey!

253
00:12:39,458 --> 00:12:40,500
[AGURI]
Now I've got you!

254
00:12:40,583 --> 00:12:42,541
Oh, hey, fancy
meeting you here!

255
00:12:42,625 --> 00:12:46,166
If you've changed your
mind about the club---

256
00:12:46,250 --> 00:12:48,000
Where have you been, Tasuku?

257
00:12:48,083 --> 00:12:49,708
I called you like a
million-bajillion times,

258
00:12:49,791 --> 00:12:50,833
but you never picked up!

259
00:12:50,916 --> 00:12:54,208
Huh? Wow, yeah you did.

260
00:12:54,291 --> 00:12:55,583
Sorry 'bout that.

261
00:12:55,666 --> 00:12:57,375
Aw...

262
00:12:57,458 --> 00:12:58,875
[DAIKI laughs]

263
00:12:58,958 --> 00:13:01,125
[MIKA] I can't believe
you just ditched her.

264
00:13:01,208 --> 00:13:02,916
[FEMALE STUDENT 2A]
Masaya, didn't you have work?

265
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:05,625
[MASAYA]
Huh? Aw, crap I forgot!

266
00:13:05,708 --> 00:13:08,583
Listen. I gotta do
something real quick.

267
00:13:08,666 --> 00:13:09,500
I'll be right back!

268
00:13:09,583 --> 00:13:11,916
But I just found you again!

269
00:13:16,583 --> 00:13:17,875
[TASUKU]
Damn it!

270
00:13:17,958 --> 00:13:19,791
What am I even doing?

271
00:13:31,208 --> 00:13:33,708
[TASUKU panting]

272
00:13:44,666 --> 00:13:45,833
[TASUKU]
Found him.

273
00:13:45,916 --> 00:13:48,208
[TASUKU]
Amano!

274
00:13:48,291 --> 00:13:49,583
[KEITA]
Uehara?

275
00:13:49,666 --> 00:13:50,750
What's up?

276
00:13:50,833 --> 00:13:53,666
Is something wrong?

277
00:13:53,750 --> 00:13:54,833
[gasps]

278
00:13:54,916 --> 00:13:56,958
[TASUKU]
Why'd you run away, huh?

279
00:13:57,041 --> 00:13:58,750
[KEITA]
Oh, that?

280
00:13:58,833 --> 00:14:00,833
There's just somewhere
I gotta be, so--

281
00:14:00,916 --> 00:14:02,875
[TASUKU]
Cut the crap!

282
00:14:04,583 --> 00:14:05,333
[KEITA]
Why?

283
00:14:05,416 --> 00:14:07,125
Does the reason even matter?

284
00:14:07,208 --> 00:14:12,291
I mean, why do you care whether
I stick around or not?

285
00:14:12,375 --> 00:14:13,500
I'm nothing.

286
00:14:13,583 --> 00:14:17,000
I'm just a nerd,
and--your life's great.

287
00:14:17,791 --> 00:14:22,208
[TASUKU] I swear to god, man.
The more I look at this kid...

288
00:14:27,208 --> 00:14:28,625
Uh. Uehara!

289
00:14:28,708 --> 00:14:31,583
Screw that nonsense! Who the
hell do you think you are?!

290
00:14:31,666 --> 00:14:33,708
Don't you tell me
my life is great!

291
00:14:33,791 --> 00:14:36,291
We play a couple a games,
and you got me figured out?

292
00:14:36,375 --> 00:14:37,791
Maybe it looks like
I got it made,

293
00:14:37,875 --> 00:14:40,041
but I had to bust my
ass to get here!

294
00:14:40,125 --> 00:14:41,500
I was a geek, too!

295
00:14:41,583 --> 00:14:44,666
I forced myself to drop
that crap, okay?

296
00:14:44,750 --> 00:14:48,000
So don't you dare write me off
as some meathead cool-kid!

297
00:14:48,083 --> 00:14:50,000
No. I'd never do that.

298
00:14:50,083 --> 00:14:51,458
Lemme guess, Amano!

299
00:14:51,541 --> 00:14:53,500
You finally bothered to
play with another person

300
00:14:53,583 --> 00:14:56,291
and it felt like a big
waste of time, didn't it?

301
00:14:56,375 --> 00:14:58,291
"You just wanna
have fun playing?"

302
00:14:58,375 --> 00:15:00,833
Yeah, like people can't hear
the shade in that answer!

303
00:15:00,916 --> 00:15:03,208
They can tell you're just
trying to avoid them!

304
00:15:03,291 --> 00:15:05,666
You think you're better
than them, but you're not!

305
00:15:05,750 --> 00:15:06,750
Look at you!

306
00:15:06,833 --> 00:15:07,958
Going to all this trouble

307
00:15:08,041 --> 00:15:10,000
so you don't have to
join some stupid club!

308
00:15:10,083 --> 00:15:11,416
But you know what?

309
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:13,416
The club is stupid, so I guess
I shouldn't give a damn

310
00:15:13,500 --> 00:15:16,875
whether Tendo drags
your sorry ass into it!

311
00:15:20,708 --> 00:15:25,333
All that, an' you're just
gonna stand there.

312
00:15:25,416 --> 00:15:26,791
[KEITA]
You take that back.

313
00:15:26,875 --> 00:15:28,041
Huh?

314
00:15:30,458 --> 00:15:31,916
[gasping]

315
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:33,583
[KEITA]
Take back what you said!

316
00:15:33,666 --> 00:15:34,958
I mean it, Uehara!

317
00:15:35,041 --> 00:15:36,291
I'm a nerd!

318
00:15:36,375 --> 00:15:38,500
I'm a random, friendless,
gaming-obsessed, nerd

319
00:15:38,583 --> 00:15:40,791
who's wasting his youth
with nothing to show for it!

320
00:15:40,875 --> 00:15:42,708
You think I somehow
missed that memo?

321
00:15:42,791 --> 00:15:44,041
Yeah, you called it.

322
00:15:44,125 --> 00:15:46,041
My answer about not wanting
to play video games

323
00:15:46,125 --> 00:15:47,666
with other people is BS!

324
00:15:47,750 --> 00:15:50,250
I'll even say games are stupid,
for the sake of this argument!

325
00:15:50,333 --> 00:15:51,666
Even though I love 'em,
I'll say it!

326
00:15:51,750 --> 00:15:53,958
I'll betray 'em!
How spineless is that?

327
00:15:54,041 --> 00:15:56,333
But that doesn't give you the
right to insult a person

328
00:15:56,416 --> 00:15:58,583
you don't even know, just
'cause they're into something...

329
00:15:58,666 --> 00:16:01,708
[TASUKU]
Crap! He's gonna kill me!

330
00:16:03,125 --> 00:16:06,416
You don't get to make
fun of her, okay?

331
00:16:06,500 --> 00:16:09,458
'Cause Tendo, she's got
a heart of gold.

332
00:16:09,541 --> 00:16:12,625
She's friendly, and
she's such a hard worker.

333
00:16:12,708 --> 00:16:16,583
And she wanted me of all
people to join her club.

334
00:16:16,666 --> 00:16:19,708
That's why you're going
to take back what you said about

335
00:16:19,791 --> 00:16:22,666
the game club that she worked
so hard to bring back to life.

336
00:16:22,750 --> 00:16:25,083
Take it back, dammit!

337
00:16:25,166 --> 00:16:27,208
All right, I take it back!
I take it all back!

338
00:16:27,291 --> 00:16:29,458
Just let go of me already,
you freak!

339
00:16:29,541 --> 00:16:31,541
Huh?

340
00:16:31,625 --> 00:16:35,916
Ah! I'm-- I'm so sorry!

341
00:16:41,583 --> 00:16:43,708
[TASUKU]
What the hell?

342
00:16:43,791 --> 00:16:46,125
It was stupid to
compare him to me.

343
00:16:46,208 --> 00:16:48,458
Just got me all pissed.

344
00:16:50,583 --> 00:16:53,416
[TASUKU]
I shouldn't've said that stuff.

345
00:16:53,500 --> 00:16:54,583
My bad.

346
00:16:54,666 --> 00:16:57,666
[KEITA]
N-No, it's fine.

347
00:16:57,750 --> 00:16:59,208
[TASUKU]
Gotta hand it to ya.

348
00:16:59,291 --> 00:17:01,958
I never thought the dude who
turned down Tendo twice

349
00:17:02,041 --> 00:17:04,833
would damn near choke me out
to defend her club's honor.

350
00:17:04,916 --> 00:17:08,166
[sputtering] I really didn't
mean to take it that far!

351
00:17:08,250 --> 00:17:10,375
[laughs sheepishly]

352
00:17:15,333 --> 00:17:17,125
[TASUKU]
Okay.

353
00:17:17,208 --> 00:17:19,541
I'm heading back to the arcade.

354
00:17:19,625 --> 00:17:22,125
So, you in?

355
00:17:22,208 --> 00:17:24,166
I'm gonna call it a day.

356
00:17:24,250 --> 00:17:27,041
There's something I want
to play back at home.

357
00:17:27,125 --> 00:17:28,750
All right.

358
00:17:28,833 --> 00:17:30,916
Well? Later, nerd.

359
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:32,208
[KEITA]
Yeah.

360
00:17:33,333 --> 00:17:35,291
[KEITA]
Oh.

361
00:17:35,375 --> 00:17:38,583
I'm sorry I just assumed that
your life was all great.

362
00:17:38,666 --> 00:17:41,250
Hey. Water under the bridge.

363
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:51,500
[TASUKU]
I was a piece of work back then,

364
00:17:51,583 --> 00:17:53,875
but this guy's got me beat.

365
00:17:53,958 --> 00:17:55,458
[KAREN gasping]

366
00:17:55,541 --> 00:17:57,625
[TASUKU]
Uh, Tendo?

367
00:18:01,833 --> 00:18:04,125
[TASUKU] I don't believe
what I'm seeing here.

368
00:18:04,208 --> 00:18:07,541
Tendo's making the
sparkle-face at him.

369
00:18:11,166 --> 00:18:13,833
[TASUKU]
Uh hey, Earth to Tendo.

370
00:18:13,916 --> 00:18:16,458
Yes, mortal.
What can I do for you?

371
00:18:16,541 --> 00:18:18,125
[KAREN cries]

372
00:18:18,208 --> 00:18:19,208
[TASUKU]
Okay, then.

373
00:18:19,291 --> 00:18:20,750
I read ya loud and clear.

374
00:18:20,833 --> 00:18:22,083
Well, good luck with that.

375
00:18:22,166 --> 00:18:24,375
[KAREN] What the what?
You get back here, mister!

376
00:18:24,458 --> 00:18:26,208
Whaddya mean, you read
me loud and clear?!

377
00:18:26,291 --> 00:18:27,750
What's so loud and clear, huh?

378
00:18:27,833 --> 00:18:29,958
And what do I need
good luck for?!

379
00:18:30,041 --> 00:18:32,666
I think that you and Amano are
gonna make a real cute couple,

380
00:18:32,750 --> 00:18:33,791
ya know what I'm sayin'?

381
00:18:33,875 --> 00:18:35,291
[KAREN yelps]

382
00:18:35,375 --> 00:18:36,958
Bye!

383
00:18:39,291 --> 00:18:41,958
[TASUKU] I can't believe
the cutest girl in school

384
00:18:42,041 --> 00:18:44,208
fell so hard for that loser.

385
00:18:44,291 --> 00:18:46,875
I'm gonna troll those
kids like a boss.

386
00:18:46,958 --> 00:18:49,333
Let the games begin, Amano!

387
00:18:49,416 --> 00:18:51,583
[AGURI growls]

388
00:18:51,666 --> 00:18:53,708
[TASUKU]
Aw, crap!

389
00:18:54,291 --> 00:18:56,500
[AGURI]
Hey, I want you to win me that.

390
00:18:56,583 --> 00:18:58,291
You've gotta be kidding me.

391
00:18:58,375 --> 00:19:00,875
Do you know how much money I've
already dropped here today?

392
00:19:00,958 --> 00:19:02,250
Uh! I knew it!

393
00:19:02,333 --> 00:19:04,375
You've been winning cute
kitties for some other girl!

394
00:19:04,458 --> 00:19:08,208
All I did was play games with
a guy from our school, okay?

395
00:19:08,291 --> 00:19:10,583
Gaming with someone
other than your girlfriend!

396
00:19:10,666 --> 00:19:13,375
Sounds like Tasuku was a big
ol' cheating cheater-face!

397
00:19:13,458 --> 00:19:15,375
[TASUKU sighs]

398
00:19:17,625 --> 00:19:20,666
♪♪♪

399
00:19:23,125 --> 00:19:26,458
[TASUKU] Me an' Aguri, we've
been dating for six months,

400
00:19:26,541 --> 00:19:30,250
but all we ever do is hang
out after school, like this.

401
00:19:30,333 --> 00:19:34,208
For real.
Why am I even with her?

402
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:36,583
Tell me something.

403
00:19:36,666 --> 00:19:39,041
What was it that made you
like me so much, anyway?

404
00:19:39,125 --> 00:19:42,375
Oh, wow! Did I really
never tell you the reason?

405
00:19:42,458 --> 00:19:44,750
[TASUKU] I betcha it's dumb,
like she dug my face.

406
00:19:44,833 --> 00:19:46,416
[AGURI]
The reason I liked you

407
00:19:46,500 --> 00:19:49,708
was because you're the
nicest guy in the world!

408
00:19:49,791 --> 00:19:51,125
[TASUKU]
Called it.

409
00:19:51,208 --> 00:19:52,958
The first time you gave me
an adorable kitty plushie

410
00:19:53,041 --> 00:19:55,208
back in middle school, I knew!

411
00:19:56,291 --> 00:20:01,041
Aw! That's not how
you get 'em out!

412
00:20:01,125 --> 00:20:04,208
Did you just say we met...
in middle school?

413
00:20:04,291 --> 00:20:05,625
[AGURI]
Mm-hm!

414
00:20:05,708 --> 00:20:07,750
I used to watch you play
the games here in the arcade,

415
00:20:07,833 --> 00:20:09,791
and you always had so much fun!

416
00:20:09,875 --> 00:20:13,250
Ever since, I've been totally
in love with you, Tasuku!

417
00:20:13,333 --> 00:20:15,375
[TASUKU]
She knew me back then?

418
00:20:15,458 --> 00:20:18,500
She knew me when I was
a nerd, and liked me?

419
00:20:18,583 --> 00:20:19,833
[gasps]

420
00:20:20,791 --> 00:20:22,375
[TASUKU]
That's right.

421
00:20:22,458 --> 00:20:24,333
I remember now.

422
00:20:24,416 --> 00:20:27,250
I'd come here sometimes
if I had a bad day,

423
00:20:27,333 --> 00:20:30,250
and there was... this girl.

424
00:20:30,333 --> 00:20:32,791
I gave it to her.

425
00:20:39,166 --> 00:20:40,625
[AGURI] Later, when I
found out we were going

426
00:20:40,708 --> 00:20:41,791
to the same high school,

427
00:20:41,875 --> 00:20:43,625
I thought, "Yay,
it's my chance!"

428
00:20:43,708 --> 00:20:46,750
But you'd turned into a real
popular guy in the meantime.

429
00:20:46,833 --> 00:20:48,416
I heard that you
liked cute girls,

430
00:20:48,500 --> 00:20:51,166
so I bought some magazines
and went for it!

431
00:20:51,250 --> 00:20:53,666
[laughs]

432
00:20:53,750 --> 00:20:55,833
[gasps] Are you okay?

433
00:20:55,916 --> 00:20:57,250
[TASUKU gasping]

434
00:21:01,416 --> 00:21:04,083
Nah, I'm fine! That's enough
hanging out for today!

435
00:21:04,166 --> 00:21:07,125
Aw! How 'bout we walk
home together, Tasuku?

436
00:21:07,208 --> 00:21:08,791
[TASUKU]
Ah! You live nearby!

437
00:21:08,875 --> 00:21:09,958
You're good for it! See ya!

438
00:21:10,041 --> 00:21:13,458
[AGURI]
Hey, wait up! Oh!

439
00:21:13,541 --> 00:21:15,125
[TASUKU]
What the hell is this?!

440
00:21:15,208 --> 00:21:18,833
My heart! It's all tingly
because of Aguri!

441
00:21:18,916 --> 00:21:21,458
She's had her eye on me
since middle school?!

442
00:21:21,541 --> 00:21:23,875
Back when I was King Nerd?!

443
00:21:25,708 --> 00:21:28,166
[TASUKU panting]

444
00:21:28,250 --> 00:21:29,416
[TASUKU]
Oh, man!

445
00:21:29,500 --> 00:21:31,500
She was so cute just now!

446
00:21:31,583 --> 00:21:34,166
Why does she look so damn
cute all of a sudden?!

447
00:21:34,250 --> 00:21:37,541
What's happening?!

448
00:21:39,291 --> 00:21:40,375
[DAIKI]
Morning.

449
00:21:40,458 --> 00:21:41,666
[TASUKU]
Yo.

450
00:21:45,500 --> 00:21:47,291
[TASUKU]
Hey, Amano.

451
00:21:47,375 --> 00:21:50,208
Uh! Hold up, you're talking
to me at school?!

452
00:21:50,291 --> 00:21:52,500
Wanted to give you the
heads-up that you were right.

453
00:21:52,583 --> 00:21:54,916
About <i>Paradigm of Phantasia.</i>

454
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:59,375
If you stumble across any other
good games, let me know.

455
00:21:59,458 --> 00:22:01,041
You got it!

456
00:22:01,125 --> 00:22:03,791
Uh, hey, man. Since when
are you buddies with Amano?

457
00:22:03,875 --> 00:22:05,750
What's it to ya?

458
00:22:05,833 --> 00:22:07,958
[DAIKI] You're in a
weirdly good mood today.

459
00:22:08,041 --> 00:22:10,000
What's that all about?

460
00:22:11,458 --> 00:22:13,250
[TASUKU]
Honestly, guys?

461
00:22:15,166 --> 00:22:17,458
Video games are the greatest!

462
00:23:52,583 --> 00:23:55,666
[STUDENT 2B] Tendo doesn't
seem herself lately.

463
00:23:59,583 --> 00:24:02,750
[EIICHI]
Oh, hey, Amano!

464
00:24:02,833 --> 00:24:03,916
So, what brings you by?

465
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:06,166
Are you here to
see Tendo, maybe?

466
00:24:06,250 --> 00:24:08,291
[KEITA]
I did drop by to see someone,

467
00:24:08,375 --> 00:24:10,291
but I'm afraid it's not her.

468
00:24:10,375 --> 00:24:11,416
[KAREN groans]

469
00:24:11,500 --> 00:24:12,583
[crash]

470
00:24:12,666 --> 00:24:13,833
[KAREN yelps]

